	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f103485464450337><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=14&mid=103485464450337>RE: Research</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=14&mid=103485464450337#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=132747><span id= >mcjtodd</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>8 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Oct 17th 7:55 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>First of all, you should wait until level 24 to start you reasearch skill. You will put one point into it and start out at skill level 24.if you start at 16, you skill level will be level 16. You can buy some research spells. If you have a premium service at Allakhazams, go to spells, necromancer and then list all to get a complete listing of spells. Click on spell infomation to get where the spell is sold or whether it is reasearch only, or NPC drop only. You could go to the Bazaar and try to buy the spells also.No, the combine on research does not always work, you will have alot of failures and loose alot of words.The words are a random drop all arcross Norrath, altho the higher the mob, the better chance of getting a higher word. I recommend you check the vendors in the zone and buy the words you need. You can go to www.castersrealm.com and get alot more information on reasech or click on the research tab here at Allakhazams. Hope this helps, good luck.<br><br>Joruliz Iskar Necromancer of 44 seasons<br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
