	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Dec 1st 4:31 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.12]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Soloing, you can generally cast one from each type of magic (magic, disease, poison, cold, fire...am I missing anything?) on a mob at the same time.&nbsp;&nbsp;There are exceptions to this.  Darkness and fear seem to be entities unto themselves and can be stacked with other magic-based spells.  The easiest way I know to tell what stacks is to look at the spell icons: each line of DoT's uses its own icon.  A higher-level spell in the same line will always overwrite and can't be overwritten by a lower-level one, and a spell cast by a higher-level player will overwrite one cast by a lower-level player.  Once again, there are some exceptions...but using this and experimentation, you should learn what stacks without much trouble.  Also, some DD spells have a residual effect after you cast it, and you have to wait for this to wear off before casting another spell from that line (Ignite bones comes to mind).  Hope this helps.<br>&nbsp;<br>Sahmhane McBhane<br>Heretic Necromancer<br>Povar<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=467528" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=467528</a></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
