	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Sep 11th 7:33 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.15]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Dark brothers of power. I commend to you the rigors of soloing in Akheva if exp is what you seek. The long corridors there are ideal for snare/fear kiting.....but you will need your wits about you. I don't recommend the entrance tunnel (too many trains) but rather the tunnel to the right of the entrance. You WILL get adds so if you haven't sorted out the judicious use of screaming terror and it concerns you to have 2-3 mobs on you at once then don't do this without a partner. But if you can pull it off - oh my - the exp is great. <br><br>I suspect you'll want to be 59th or 60th to try solo (and if not get a buddy). Personally I sic pet, then Pyro, then Splurt, then Devour, then Fear, then Ebolt and only then do I sit to med with a root memed in case the mob wanders too close to others. When adds come I ST - sit - ST - sit until the first mob is toast then repeat. By pulling mobs way down the hall (by sitting to get them aggro towards you and off pet) before fearing you can ensure you have room to fear. You are likely to need to swap spells mid fight at times to keep buffed etc.<br><br>NB This + rogue combo = outrageous murder if you want to have the security of a buddy and up the DPS ;P<br>&nbsp;<br>Falrinth Twysted<br>65 Dark Elven Arch Lich<br>Second Age<br>Cazic Thule</td></tr>
