	   <a name=10317555717609></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f10317555717609><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=14&mid=10317555717609>RE: Akheva solo or duo</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=14&mid=10317555717609#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=153229><span id=Sage>Falrinth</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>35 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Sep 11th 11:00 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.25]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Dalthin, level 42 is a tough one because you are still a few levels off a significant power increase. However you should be able to solo pretty well in Overthere to the right of the entrance to Sky Fire (right if walking out of the tunnel entrance) or by the Outpost. Most necros can go into the outpost and are not KOS but some are (notably Iksars) so this is not an option if you are KOS there because the roaming DE guards will own you. Collect Sarnak Berzerker tails and give them to the undead captian 4 at a time for faction that will one day lead to receiving a Worker Sledgemallet (handy at 50+ - no proc until then....quest required that is dead easy once you ahve the faction). If you are KOS in Outpost then the southern corner of the zone is normally safe from guards (but look out!).<br><br>You might be able to handle the weaker Spirocs in Timorous Deep but I doubt you'll manage well without more support. Once at 44th these are outstanding exp solo but still tough and you need to know the ropes pretty well so as not to pull too many at once and not to try Provens and Watchers for a while longer. The same applies to Dreadlands wall.<br><br>Grouped in Kaesora (full team of 38-44) is not only fun and great exp but also great practise for dungeon play. You can use your undead slow spells to great effect as well.......though this option is only if you are KOS in Outpost since killing in Kaesora screws your Venril Sathir (Outpost faction) so take care. Don't do this with clowns.<br><br>So, recommendations:<br><br>Solo = Overthere <br>Small group of 2-4 = Spirocs or Dreadlands<br>Mean team of good players (6) = Kaesora (faction depending)<br><br>My recollections of 42 are a bit hazey so please read up further on these before taking up these suggestions. I'm a player who likes a challenge not dull grinding easy stuff so may have pitched this at a level of difficulty a bit over what a 42nd necro can handle - but hey, there's only one way to find out right? If you want to be safe watch others in these places and group with them first to get a feel.<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Falrinth Twysted<br>65 Dark Elven Arch Lich<br>Second Age<br>Cazic Thule</td></tr>
